    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.themes.Item.imZk4tj2asyTA01f]{Giantblood}</p>\n<p>You can exert yourself in a burst of tremendous strength. As a standard action, you can use two free hands to hurl a single piece of debris as a ranged attack with a @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Nrf6oy9pJwcEmryP.JournalEntryPage.nXkFsyxk7Vybdn7G#thrown]{thrown} weapon that targets KAC. Debris is otherwise treated as an @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Nrf6oy9pJwcEmryP.JournalEntryPage.21wLdW9boKwLHuxn]{improvised weapon} (Core Rulebook 169) that deals 1d6 bludgeoning damage per bulk and has a range increment equal to 5 × your Strength modifier. Debris can be any object with a minimum bulk of 3 and a maximum bulk equal to your Strength modifier + 2 ([[@abilities.str.mod + 2]]), but that object must be unattended or readily torn from the environment (at the GM’s discretion). Picking up such debris is a move action. You can’t use this ability while @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.OwZA6flUQPH0jPA0]{Encumbered} or @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.11k3ObUIXEYFGrg9]{Overburdened}.</p>"
